		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=ColdCell&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Hello, I am playing WoW as my first MMORPG. But lately I'm getting bored with it... so I heard about EQ and the tons of game content. <br /> <br />Can anyone point out the good things and bad things about EQ against WoW?&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Richmond Hill, Ontario, Canada</td><td align="right" id="fs8" >16 Replies</td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td>

		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Mar 24th 6:03 AM2005 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=1111658303157143285&num=16&page=0&post=1&replyto=1111662142179732825"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1111662142179732825></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=543517"><span id="">Glauron</span></a><b><span id=""></span></b><br />45 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Glauron&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Howdy ColdCell. I have played EQ on and off (mostly on) for the past 4 years. I have not logged in for about 6 months but getting ready to again. I played WoW for a while, but being an avid EQ1 junkie, it just wasn't for me.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />Main differences, (I assume you mean EQ1, not 2?) <br />Classes and races. Unlike WoW, depending on which race you choose, you only have a limited scope for class choice. Ie..... <br />Choose a half elf as your race, you can only play as a certain class. A half elf cannot play a Cleric but may become a Bard....etc etc.....(which I think is a good thing). <br />Spells. Rather than have a class trainer who teaches you all your spells, you need to buy them from a vendor/npc. Some will need to be quested for (though not to many) or dropped from a mob. <br />Game graphics. You need to remember that EQ is quite an old game in the scale of things. Although it's evolved along the way, the graphic of the game is far from cutting edge. Still looks nice though, and has a really nice feel to it. WoW, although looking good seemed very cartoonish to me. EQ Graphics and atmosphere feels alot more, well, real for wan't of a better word. I've found it easier to get into character and sit back and enjoy than WoW or EQ2. <br /> To compare the 2 , you could almost use the phrase &quot;chalk and cheese&quot;. On a basic level they're in essence, the same thing. Start a toon, kill lots of things to gain exp/lvl's, better equipment and weapons and hopefully have fun along the way, but deep down they are completely different, both in look and feel. <br />I'm sort of sorry I replied now as you could go on and on describing the differences between the two, and my fingers are hurtin' already. <br /> I guess my advice to you is just go and try it. From what I hear these days, there are a few newbie servers around where you could almost dive into the old EQ days and have a ball. Plenty of grp's and young toons to &quot;add to friends list&quot;! <br />Pretty cheap to try. In Australia you can pick up EQ platinum which is I think is the original plus all the expansions bar 1 for about $50. $30 in Canada I believe. So good value all in all. Send me a message and i'll make a toon on your server if you like and we can be newbies together!</p>
</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td>

