		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=306634"><span id="Scholar">LanceValiant</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />261 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.23]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=LanceValiant&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Hmmmm. <br /> <br />Seems to me this will go one of two ways, either you will get lots of help, or the flames will start pouring in. <br /> <br />I'll start by attempting to set the course to 'Help'. <br /> <br />Although I've never played WoW, I've read a little.&nbsp;&nbsp;I've played EQ a little over the course of a year.  The one main thing I notice with regularity in the difference between the two games is that while WoW seems to be a : <br />light hearted, <br />pop in and out, <br />short play time possible, <br />quickly rise in level, <br />nothing too serious, <br />giggle kind of a game. <br /> <br />EQ is much more of a : <br />very deep, <br />massive content, <br />play a year and scratch the surface, <br />huge timesink, <br />level more slowy, <br />read around it as much as you play it, <br />slightly more mature, <br />organised, <br />way of life for some type of game. <br /> <br />Of course that is only my opinion. <br /> <br />The graphics and differences in tradeskills etc are slightly less important to me but remember EQ is a much older game.  EQ2 is somewhere in the middle me thinks and of course is brand new with pretty graphics and everything. <br /> <br />As far as play styles goes that seems to be it, but as far as differences in the games make-up, they are endless and I'll leave someone else to describe them.</p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Kronkin, Dwarf Paladin of the 40th Tour - Povar Rasp <br /> <br />Roll on Aude Sapere.</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Wokingham, England</td></tr></table>
