<p>All those breaking pages must die. <br />Oh, it's Elorian.&nbsp;&nbsp;Figures =-P <br /> <br />Correct your shiz. <br /> <br />To the OP -- Why exactly are you bored with WoW? Are you level 60 doing instance run after instance run? Level 10 and you just have ADD? Give us a little more info and we can probably not help you, but pretend really well that we are doing so. <br /> <br />If you're level 60, yeah, EQ end-game is going to be much more healthy than WoW endgame.....assuming you can get into the right sort of raiding guild, who happens to be doing content you're capable of doing. <br /> <br />But, don't expect to get up there in levels like you do in WoW.  EQ, even though it's MUCH more newbie friendly than before, still takes a lot more work to level than WoW does.  And even after you've leveled, there's the whole thing about grinding out AA's (yay.  Fun.  Not.)  Think of AA's as something like talent points, but you can save up a crapload of them, and use them to buy different abilities starting at level 51 (but most suggest waiting until around level 60 at least to work on AAs).  When you  earn AA experience, it takes away from your main experience...so you level slower.  Whatever, I won't get too much into that. <br /> <br /> <br />Anyway, if you're a very low level in WoW and are already bored, then MMOs might not be the type of game for you...because EQ moves a *lot* slower than WoW as far as leveling is concerned. <br /> <br />Also, if you're a heavy soloer, you're going to get pretty bored.  I know in both EQ and WoW, it was almost always much more fun to group with a friend. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sat Mar 26 00:19:54 2005 by emperorjeremy</span></i></p>
